        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 5:49PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 549 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Thorntonville, or near Monahans, moving south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Monahans, Thorntonville, Grandfalls, Wickett, Royalty, and Roy Hurd
Memorial Airport.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 69 and 83.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
